    {
      "id": "d385c43e978ac54ffed47c3257159b856da1103c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-11-25 06:22:36.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nI don't understand why this needs a separate portal?  Shouldn't the unified target code be able to handle the different targets by UUID like it does for different OSTs or MDTs on the same node?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "3acb4a4552fe050af6d17b128e8dbff7ecfe2940",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-11-25 09:49:44.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nI thought Mike has a solution for this already?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "e212b1ee42c6f31de61c8c0bf9f73d6e519dac0c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 118,
        "name": "Mikhail Pershin",
        "email": "mpershin@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "tappro"
      },
      "date": "2013-11-25 11:12:56.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nCould you explain what kind of problem you have with this? Both OUT services are identical now and there should be no problems or conflicts. The only issue remains is reply portal which is different. I have patch to fix that by using OSC_REPLY_PORTAL for both OST and MDT and Alex confirmed it works well with his patches, maybe you have the same problem?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "a5decf384a35ed137531498694935aa30d8395f8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2013-11-27 08:21:59.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nI met the same issue in my LFSCK patches. My solution is NOT change from MDC_REPLY_PORTAL to OSC_REPLY_PORTAL, but from OSC_REPLY_PORTAL to MDC_REPLY_PORTAL. Because the released Lustre-2.4/Lustre-2.5 has already used MDC_REPLY_PORTAL for cross-MDT operations. How to handle cross-MDT interoperability issues if use OSC_REPLY_PORTAL?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "64331caff8fa272f74f22d12aca15a238b380b82",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 118,
        "name": "Mikhail Pershin",
        "email": "mpershin@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "tappro"
      },
      "date": "2013-11-27 20:35:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nFan Yong, with osc_reply_portal we will need to change only MDTs all together, with mdc_reply_portal we will need to upgrade MDT and OST at the same time, I think upgrading MDTs is much easier task",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "c60955daa6a28d97fa21b632d7b215e2384e9483",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-11-27 20:50:49.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nAlso note that Di is landing a patch that changes the OUT RPC protocol in 2.6, so the MDS nodes will all need to be updated together anyway.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
